# Frontend Web Application Behavior

## Page Structure
All HTML pages use consistent structure with UTF-8 encoding (`<meta charset="UTF-8">`) for emoji support.

### [web/index.html](mdc:web/index.html) - Landing Page
- Navigation buttons for Chess, Ping Pong, Backgammon
- Monica Geller quote: "If we're not keeping score, how do we know who's having the most fun?"
- Server status indicator (green = online, red = offline)
- JavaScript checks API health at `http://ec2-3-81-147-93.compute-1.amazonaws.com:8080/api/health`

### Game Pages Pattern
Each game page ([chess.html](mdc:web/chess.html), [pingpong.html](mdc:web/pingpong.html), [backgammon.html](mdc:web/backgammon.html)) follows same pattern:

#### UI Elements
- **üè† Home** button - Returns to [index.html](mdc:web/index.html)
- **Leaderboard** button - Toggles `{game}_leaderboard.png` display
- **Ratings Progress** button - Toggles `{game}_ratings_progress.png` display  
- **‚ûï Add Player** button - Opens modal form for new player creation

#### Add Player Modal
- Modal overlay with form for player name input
- JavaScript makes POST request to `/api/players/{game}` endpoint
- Shows loading state during API call
- Displays success/error messages
- Auto-refreshes page on successful player addition

## API Integration
- All API calls use HTTP (not HTTPS) to avoid certificate complexity
- CORS-enabled for cross-origin requests (S3/CloudFront ‚Üí EC2)
- Graceful error handling for offline server scenarios

## Image Handling
- Player images: `web/images/players/{name}.png`
- Medal icons: `web/images/medals/{1st,2nd,3rd}.png`
- Generated charts: `web/{game}_leaderboard.png` and `web/{game}_ratings_progress.png`